    <dt>Verify</dt>
	<dt>setup the timezone</dt>
    <dt>At partitioning select "Guided</dt>
	<dt>- Use entire disk"</dt>
    <dt>Select disk to partition</dt>
		<dd>[FILL VERIFICATION]</dd>
    <dt>At "Write changes to disks"</dt>
	<dt>verify that everythings is right</dt>
	<dt>select YES</dt>
    <dt>At "http proxy" request, leave it blank</dt>
	<dt>press enter</dt>
    <dt>At managing upgrades select "No automatic updates"</dt>
		<dd>[FILL VERIFICATION]</dd>
    <dt>At Software</dt>
	<dt>selection, choose "Virtual Machine host" with arrows</dt>
	<dt>select it with "space bar"</dt>
	<dt>confirm with "Enter"</dt>
    <dt>Select to install Grub in the master boot record</dt>
		<dd>[FILL VERIFICATION]</dd>
    <dt>Remove the installation media (CDROM or USB key)</dt>
		<dd>[FILL VERIFICATION]</dd>
    <dt>Wait that the system reboot</dt>
	<dt>login</dt>
    	<dd>Verify that ubuntu-virt-server package is installed:</dd>
        <dd>dpkg -l ubuntu-virt-server</dd>
    	<dd>Verify that you have KVM-capable hardware:</dd>
        <dd>kvm-ok</dd>
        <dd>has to return that KVM acceleration can be used</dd>
    	<dd>Verify that the KVM kernel module is loaded</dd>
        <dd>lsmod | grep kvm</dd>        
